msItem.explicit:
dez man erdenken kant
mit maister

Nyerup, Symbolæ literaturam Teutonicam antiqviorem ex codicibus manu exaratis, qvi Havniæ asservantur 1-82

supportDesc.foliation: Foliated 1-60 in red ink by Kristian Kålund in the upper right-hand corners.
supportDesc.condition: The manuscript is in a very good condition with leaves of a beautiful, parchment in a light colour.

layout.p: Written in single columns with 25 lines per page. The text measures: 160 90

handNote.p: Written in German gothic cursive in a large and flourished hand.

decoNote.p: Large opening initial E at f. 2r, a littera florissa in blue and gold.
At f. 36r a large blue and red initial is found.

additions.p: On f. 1r (the first flyleaf) a short note in Italian exists.

binding.p: The manuscript has a half binding with spine and corners of parchment and side-coverings of marbled paper, 249 177 25 On the front paste-down Kristian Kålund has noted the date 7/i [19]09.

origin.p: Written in Germany. Kålund ( Katalog I 24 ) dated the manuscript to ca 1400, while Heinzle (Mittelhochdeutsche Dietrichepik145, 298f.) later dated it more precisely to the first quarter of the fifteenth century.

source.p: Catalogued 22. september 1999 af EW-J based on Kålund's catalogue.

custEvent.p: During conservation from 17 June to 4 September 1997, the paper used to attached the the first and second quires was removed and replaced with white stitching threads of flax.
The manuscript was photographed before restoration but the date is not registered.
Portraits of the spine and the upper board, the spine, openings of the book: fols 48v-49r, opening: spine and lower section were taken 27 June 1997.
Supplementary photographs were taken of the first fly-leaf v, the last fly-leaf v, the last paste down and 39r 8 July 1999 and 21 January 1999..
Colour photographs of fols 2r, 11r and 36r were taken 16 September 1997 (after restoration).

list.item: Neg. pocket, 2 and 4, from 27 June 1997 (photographs of the spine, opening: ff. 48v-49r and bottom of ff. 48v-49r).
Microfilm (originals), Neg. 997, 8 June 1997., (supplementary photographs of the verso of the flyleafs, lower pastedown and f. 39r).
Microfilm (archive), Arkiv 910, from 21 January 1999 (supplementary photographs of the verso of the flyleafs, lower pastedown and f. 39r).
